INSERT INTO `main_site_projectitem` VALUES (1,'I','IMG_0937_adjusted_crop_smaller.jpg','154.jpg','',4,6,1,6,'Before there was a pine bedside table with a rattan chair.','The bed with a bedside table painted grey, with the new white chair.'),(2,'T','','','The previously all grey room has been updated with dusky pink walls to create a softer, romantic feel. Toning pale blues from the cushions and curtains, together with the stronger greens in the artwork and plants all combine to make a harmonious, restful colour scheme.',3,2,3,6,'',''),(3,'I','IMG_0980.jpg','109_XgYjGkZ.jpg','',2,7,2,6,'Before the chest of drawers was pine, and the walls were grey.','A view of the chest of drawers which has been painted grey, in front of the pink painted walls.'),(4,'T','','','With the floors and doors stripped back to the original wood, the old pine furniture looked dated and in need of a refresh. Now painted in a soft grey, it looks perfectly suited to a period property. Storage which is reminiscent of old fashioned steamer trunks add a stylish twist, blending old and new, and a mixture of metals in the chrome handles, copper lighting and brass mirror add visual interest.',2,7,9,6,'',''),(5,'I','IMG_0920_cropped_8hivdaU.jpg','102.jpg','',5,7,14,6,'Before the wall behind the bed was in a grey wallpaper,  with no artwork and pine bedside tables.','A photo of the bed with the new picture ledge and artwork above.'),(6,'I','IMG_1010.jpg','','',2,3,12,6,'','A close up of the chest of drawers which have been painted grey, and new handles added.'),(7,'I','IMG_0993.jpg','IMG_20171118_153449.jpg','',2,7,11,6,'Before, the wardrobe was pine, with brown storage boxes on top.','A photo of the wardrobe which has been painted grey, with the colourful storage trunks on top.'),(8,'I','IMG_0956.jpg','108.jpg','',4,6,13,6,'Before the walls were painted grey and the furniture was pine.','A view of the fireplace with the new pink painted walls, plants on the mantle piece and the grey painted furniture in the alcoves.'),(9,'I','IMG_1004.jpg','','',3,4,6,6,'','A close up of the new brass dimmer switch on a white back plate.'),(10,'I','IMG_0985.jpg','110_cropped.jpg','',3,9,5,6,'The old glass table lamp with a grey lampshade, on top of the pine chest of drawers.','A close up of the new pink textured lamp with a green palm print lampshade on top of the grey chest of drawers.'),(11,'I','IMG_0951_lighter3.jpg','119_adjusted.jpg','',5,7,7,6,'A view of the window with the original four curtains looking messy.','A view of the bed and the windows with the four original blue curtains made into two. There are also new white painted wooden Venetian blinds.'),(12,'I','IMG_0989.jpg','168.jpg','',2,7,10,6,'Before, the walls were grey and there were blue and yellow vases on the mantle piece.','A photo of two brass plant pots with plants on the mantle piece.'),(13,'T','','','A clever mix of contemporary and traditional. Elements of copper, brass and chrome, combine with geometric shapes in the soft furnishings and lamp to give the room a relaxed but edgy look.',1,6,8,6,'',''),(14,'I','IMG_0960_cropped.jpg','114_6wKCxyG.jpg','',3,6,4,6,'Before the wardrobe was pine and had brown storage boxes on top.','The grey painted wardrobe with new colourful storage trunks on top.'),(15,'I','IMG_2003_with_bowl.jpg','IMG_20190105_154316.jpg','',4,6,1,12,'A photo of the same angle of the kitchen area with the units partially installed and bare plaster walls.','A photo of the kitchen area with light grey cabinets, marble worktops and a funky green geometric tile for the splashback.'),(16,'T','','','A new extension creates a larger kitchen, dining and living space and adds lots of light from the partially glazed roof and bi-fold doors. A carefully chosen palette of soft greens, mustard yellows and warm blues, along with touches of copper and brass combine to make a welcoming living space.',2,3,2,12,'',''),(17,'I','IMG_1989_straight.jpg','IMG_20190105_154740.jpg','',2,7,3,12,'A photo of the same angle with bare plaster walls and temporary uPVC sliding doors.','A photo of the new light oak flooring, the dining table and the yellow, green and grey dining chairs.'),(18,'I','IMG_1951_altered_2.jpg','IMG_20190105_154704.jpg','',4,6,4,12,'A photo of the same angle with bare plaster walls, some of the kitchen units stacked up and temporary uPVC sliding doors.','A photo of the pale green sofa, oak coffee table and the kitchen area and dining table behind.'),(19,'I','IMG_1970.jpg','','',3,7,13,12,'','A close up of the walnut sunburst clock on the wall.'),(20,'I','IMG_1973_with_pictures.jpg','IMG_20190105_154656.jpg','',2,7,6,12,'A photo of the same angle with bare plaster walls, and before the wood burning stove was installed.','A photo of the yellow armchair with the colourful rug and the built in shelves and wood burning stove in the background.'),(21,'T','','','Striking geometric patterns run throughout the design, giving the eye something interesting to see in every direction.',2,3,8,12,'',''),(22,'I','IMG_1943.jpg','IMG_20190105_154731.jpg','',5,6,12,12,'A photo of the same angle before the shelving was built, with bare plaster walls and some of the kitchen units stacked up.','A view of the green painted built in shelving, with the Frame TV on the wall, and the sofa and yellow armchair.'),(23,'I','IMG_1999_cropped.jpg','IMG_20190105_154313.jpg','',4,6,9,12,'A photo of the same angle with bare plaster walls and chipboard covering where the glass roof will go.','A photo of the three wall lights in the extension area, with the glass roof above.'),(24,'T','','','The textures, colours and patterns of the design soften the harder lines of the kitchen area, and visually link it with the cosier lounge area, making the whole space work.',1,5,17,12,'',''),(25,'I','IMG_2012_for_insta_xkNxaBj.jpg','','',2,4,10,12,'','A close up of the built in shelves styled with gin bottles, a plant and artwork.'),(26,'I','IMG_1521_cropped_more_tap.jpg','IMG_20190105_154102.jpg','',3,7,14,12,'A photo of the kitchen area with the old window, bare plaster walls and no window dressing.','A photo showing the kitchen window with the green painted wall around it, and the new colourful Roman blind.'),(27,'I','IMG_1972_cropped.jpg','','',2,3,5,12,'','A close up of some gin bottles which are on the built in shelves.'),(28,'I','IMG_1994_qvPLZFt.jpg','IMG_20190105_154235.jpg','',5,6,15,12,'A photo of the area were the sofa is now, with the boarding and temporary  uPVC sliding doors.','A view of the pale green sofa with the oak coffee table and fresh flowers in front.'),(29,'T','','','Pops of colour added inside the stove surround, on the tiled splashback and in the accessories turn this space into something unexpected and special.',4,1,11,12,'',''),(30,'I','IMG_1194.jpg','287_cropped.jpg','',2,7,13,9,'The old bath with grey tiles and a bare wall above.','A photo of the corner above the bath, showing the hanging planters, the plant on the window sill, and the mustard yellow blind at the window.'),(31,'I','IMG_1463_8S2faEH.jpg','302_c8bVf9y.jpg','',3,8,3,9,'A photo of the old sink area which had a single pedestal sink with the chrome towel radiator to the side.','A photo of the new shower screen with the new double sinks behind, with new yellow blinds at the windows.'),(32,'T','','','A complete re-design of a family bathroom in an Edwardian terrace gives the family a modern, bright space. A dramatic dark grey wall colour, contrasted with white metro tiles, mustard yellow blinds and some greenery make the room feel contemporary yet classic.',3,2,4,9,'',''),(33,'I','IMG_1436_straight.jpg','','',2,7,2,9,'','A close up of the new chrome shower valve in the shower area.'),(34,'I','IMG_1435_straightened.jpg','','',2,4,14,9,'','A close up of the two sinks with their tall chrome taps next to them.'),(35,'T','','','The brief called for double sinks, an open shower area and a large, comfortable bath to relax in. A flexible lighting design on separate circuits and with dimmer switches gives bright task lighting when needed, and more subdued light to help unwind after a long day.',2,3,16,9,'',''),(36,'I','IMG_1411.jpg','287_tFeIUlU.jpg','',4,6,1,9,'The same view of the old brown painted bath with grey tiles and brown mosaic tiles behind.','A photo of the bathroom showing the bath, window with new blind, dark walls and metro tiles with hanging planters.'),(37,'I','IMG_1446_bigger.jpg','285_BxSZcSa.jpg','',5,6,7,9,'A photo of the airing cupboard door, with a bare wall where the towel radiator was moved to.','The oak airing cupboard door with a new hook on the back, and the chrome towel radiatior in it\'s new position.'),(38,'I','IMG_1440_cropped.jpg','','',2,6,15,9,'','A close up of the standpipe bath tap and shower head, seen through the plant hanging over the window sill.'),(39,'T','','','A wall hung loo and a concealed cistern give the illusion of more space.',4,1,10,9,'',''),(40,'I','IMG_1454_cropped_umsWF6V.jpg','288_te59lg6.jpg','',4,6,9,9,'The same view with the old loo with the towel radiator next to it.','A view of the low false wall which has the wall hung loo and the double sinks on it.'),(41,'T','','','A niche created in the shower area provides storage for toiletries, and the clever lighting inside it gives the space a soft glow in the evenings.',1,5,6,9,'',''),(42,'I','IMG_1386_less_colour_cropped_9pfYXc0.jpg','286_cropped.jpg','',4,6,11,9,'The old glass door to the shower enclosure, showing the smaller shower area.','A photo of the new open shower area with one panel screen and a niche for toiletries.'),(43,'I','IMG_1442.jpg','','',2,7,12,9,'','A close up photo of the three woven hanging planters with plants in them, hanging in the corner of the bathroom.'),(44,'I','IMG_1116_adjusted_crop_smaller_zAm1Q93.jpg','Copy_of_2274.jpg','',5,6,1,7,'A photo of the space before the wall was knocked down.','A photo of the kitchen area with light grey cabinets, white Corian worktops and a floor lamp in the foreground.'),(45,'T','','','A small, dark kitchen in the middle of the house is opened up by knocking down two walls and removing internal doors and a window. The cooking area has been moved so the chef is now at the centre of the action, and a sofa and armchair have been added to create a sociable family space.',1,6,2,7,'',''),(46,'I','IMG_1137.jpg','2174_OS239Un.jpg','',4,6,9,7,'A photo of the old internal doors and frames which were blocking out light.','The internal doors have been taken down and there is a new dining table and chairs here now.'),(47,'I','IMG_1073.jpg','','',2,7,10,7,'','A close up of the mantle piece with a black vase, black candlestick and a copper bowl on top.'),(48,'I','IMG_1044_new_fireplace.jpg','','',4,6,13,7,'','The new seating area and dining area with pink walls.'),(49,'I','IMG_1097.jpg','2273_4KdT74v.jpg','',4,6,7,7,'Before the space was opened up, the internal doors and arch into the kitchen made the space feel dark and too small.','The kitchen space has been opened up into the dining area.'),(50,'T','','','A tall bank of kitchen units makes the most of limited wall space and provides a huge amount of storage.',4,1,6,7,'',''),(51,'T','','','A soft, muted pink on the walls makes the kitchen units almost disappear, and works perfectly with the warm copper tones of the lighting and breakfast bar. A washable but matt paint finish is also practical for a hardworking family kitchen.',2,5,15,7,'',''),(52,'I','IMG_1139.jpg','','',4,6,4,7,'','A close up of the two copper pendant lamps which hang over the hob area.'),(53,'I','IMG_1092.jpg','','',4,5,11,7,'','A close up of the new white bar stools against the copper on the back of the kitchen units.'),(54,'I','IMG_1126_cropped.jpg','','',2,5,12,7,'','A close up of the new black pendant light in the seating area.'),(55,'I','IMG_1082_adjusted_crop_smaller_itNXYND.jpg','2175_rWjUsUc.jpg','',5,7,14,7,'A view of the internal doors before they were taken out.','A photo of the opened up dining area, looking through to the seating area.'),(56,'I','IMG_1111_cropped.jpg','2272.jpg','',2,7,5,7,'The room before had internal doors leading to the conservatory.','A view of the sunlight streaming into the kitchen through the windows, highlighting the potted plant and black floor lamp.'),(57,'I','IMG_1071_straightened.jpg','073.jpg','',4,6,17,7,'A photo showing the old wall which was blocking the view from the kitchen to the dining room.','This photo shows how knocking the wall down has created a connection to the rest of the room.'),(58,'T','','','Touches of black echo the colour of the original fireplace, and help to balance the whites and pale colours used elsewhere.',2,3,8,7,'',''),(59,'I','Living_room_4_GpyTe9D.jpg','Living_Room_Before_0GAFAZx.jpg','',5,7,1,2,'The living room was painted cream with a shiny turquoise feature wallpaper.','A view of the now colourful living room, with all new furniture and accessories.'),(60,'T','','','A property in the beautiful Brecon Beacons was turned into a bright and welcoming holiday rental. The finishes needed to be bold and contemporary, but also practical and timeless.',1,7,2,2,'',''),(61,'T','','','',0,0,17,2,'',''),(62,'I','Living_room_4_cropped_3.jpg','','',2,7,3,2,'','A close up of the red, orange and grey cushions on the grey sofa.'),(63,'I','Living_room_no_car.jpg','SAM_1937_adjusted.jpg','',4,5,4,2,'Before the living room was empty, with magnolia walls and turquoise overlong curtains.','Another view of the living room showing the dark blue feature wall, grey armchair and colourful curtains and rug.'),(64,'T','','','Each room has it\'s own distinctive mid-century style, with colour used to provide a sense of unity.',2,1,7,2,'',''),(65,'I','IMG_1980_cropped4.jpg','','',2,4,7,12,'','A photo of the green geometric tile splash back in the kitchen area.'),(66,'T','','','',1,5,16,12,'',''),(67,'I','IMG_0998_cropped.jpg','','',2,3,15,6,'','A close up of the new artwork on the wall above the bed, on a white picture shelf.'),(68,'T','','','An eclectic mix of artwork with personal value adds the finishing touch to the room.',1,7,16,6,'',''),(69,'I','IMG_1439_cropped.jpg','296_spAmgu0.jpg','',3,5,5,9,'The old enclosed shower area with a glass door on a built in cubicle.','A close up of the new shower screen with the chrome shower head and metro tiles behind.'),(70,'I','IMG_2039_straightened.jpg','','',2,7,8,9,'','A close up of the shower niche with lighting inside, showing off the nice body wash bottles.'),(71,'I','IMG_1069_cropped.jpg','','',2,3,3,7,'','A close up some chopping boards leaning against the worktop and the pink walls.'),(72,'T','','','The period features have been retained, keeping the house\'s character, but the kitchen is everything you\'d expect from a modern family home.',2,5,16,7,'',''),(73,'I','Kitchen_uf6BAb5.jpg','SAM_1940_Ato5fVb.jpg','',4,5,5,2,'The same kitchen units, but without furniture or accessories.','A photo of the kitchen with new bar stools, dining table and chairs and colourful artwork.'),(74,'I','Main_bedroom_2_cropped_wider.jpg','SAM_1942_casLALA.jpg','',4,6,15,2,'A photo of the room before which had a brown feature wall and beige and brown curtains.','A photo of the master bedroom with a blue feature wall, grey, yellow and blue curtains and coordinating accessories.'),(75,'I','Main_bedroom_2cropped2.jpg','','',2,3,9,2,'','A close up of the artwork in the master bedroom on the blue feature wall.'),(76,'I','Bathroom_with_blinds_darker.jpg','SAM_1954_hQUsWzV.jpg','',3,5,12,2,'Before, the bathroom just had a basic white bathroom suite.','A photo of the bathroom with grey and yellow styling touches added.'),(77,'I','Bedroom_4_adjusted.jpg','SAM_1952_58Q7q0d.jpg','',4,7,10,2,'Before the room was bare, with no furniture and white painted walls.','A photo of one of the single bedrooms, with yellow and grey bedding and coordinating curtains.'),(78,'I','Bed_3_2_cropped.jpg','SAM_1949_Ccw0edk.jpg','',2,4,13,2,'Before this was an empty girl\'s bedroom with a pink feature wall and decorative wall